article.headline: Brown 64, Columbia 59
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Damon Huffman scored a game-high 22 points to lead Brown to a 64-59 victory over Columbia on Friday night. Mark MacDonald added 13 points, and Mark McAndrew had 12 to help Brown (10-16, 5-6 Ivy League) win its third straight game. John Baumann led Columbia (13-12, 4-7) with 14 points and seven rebounds, and Brett Loscalzo and Montgomery added 11 points each.
